ligion, caste, class, gender, language, and region in India, the book proposes a new politics of revitalized federalism. Intended for a general readership, and eschewing academic jargon, this book will be of interest to anyone concerned about the future of India.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aDemocracyzIndia. 0aHindutva. 0aNationalismzIndiaxHistory. 4aAsian Studies : India and South Asian Studies. 4aCultural Studies : Postcolonial Studies. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Hindu Studies. 7aHISTORY / Asia / India & South Asia.2bisacsh1 aChatterjee, Partha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChatterjee, Partha, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2022z978311149185140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143848778640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438487786423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438487786/original  a978-3-11-149185-1  SUNY Press eBook Package 2022b2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles